The paper proposes a Bayesian algorithm for sparse representation, which involves statistical inference and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of correlations and activity measures, which are related to machine learning and statistical modeling, respectively. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents simulation results, which involve performance evaluation and computational complexity analysis, indicating that cs.SI (Systems and Control) could also be a relevant sub-category.
